The pinned upstream commit, fetch date, and a description of the
modifications applied (subset selection + YAML-to-JSON conversion) are
recorded in this directory's `SBS_VERSION` and `NOTICE` files, and in the
`_license` block at the top of `controls.json`. The canonical attribution
text that the skill's `SKILL.md` requires to be rendered verbatim at the
end of every audit response lives in `ATTRIBUTION.txt`.

Per CC BY-SA 4.0 section 3(b), any work that adapts the material in this
directory and is then redistributed must itself be licensed under
CC BY-SA 4.0 (or a later-compatible Creative Commons license). The
boundary of that obligation is this directory: code elsewhere in this
skill (and the broader repository) that *reads* these files is not itself
an adaptation of the licensed material and is unaffected by the
ShareAlike term.

`controls.json`, `SBS_VERSION`, and `ATTRIBUTION.txt` are auto-generated
by `scripts/fetch_sbs.py`. Do not edit them by hand — submit corrections
upstream at the source repository linked above.

Per the SBS project's community naming guidance, we do not use the names
"SBS" or "Security Benchmark for Salesforce" to brand a modified or forked
version. We use the names only to identify the upstream standard we audit
against, per the project's stated acceptable use ("Built for SBS
compliance", "SBS-compatible scanner").
